The Extended Combine Shipment (ECS) app is used as a substitute for the standard Business Central function "Cumulative Invoicing" and allows you to:

* Define "invoicing methods" to specify the grouping criteria of documents based on the customer.
* Set invoicing frequency to determine the shipping recovery period.
* Speed up the process of generating preliminary sales invoices.
* Schedule the invoicing process.
* Subject the invoicing process to Data Security Workflow.
* Assign a specific document class to invoices generated automatically by ECS.
* Automatically insert recurring lines (e.g., fees, periodic services) into invoices generated by ECS and decide whether to create a separate service invoice or append them to the goods invoices generated by shipments.
